---
import Default from '../layouts/Default.astro';
import Hero from '../components/Hero.astro';
import SectionHead from '../components/SectionHead.astro';
---
<Default title="About · Harshith Kantamneni" description="I build autonomous AI labs and write about how they fail." current="about">

  <Hero
    meta={['Milwaukee, Wisconsin', 'Building AI labs full-time']}
  >
    I build autonomous<br />AI labs.
  </Hero>

  <SectionHead marker="WORK" title="What I do" />

  <div class="page-grid">
    <div class="extended measure-tight drop-cap">
      <p>I design and run autonomous AI labs full-time. The work is figuring out how to get multi-agent systems to do useful engineering and research without a human in the loop, and being honest about what they actually accomplish versus what they only appear to accomplish.</p>
      <p>The interesting problem isn't getting agents to produce output. They produce plenty. The interesting problem is getting them to produce output that survives contact with the world. Most multi-agent setups quietly break that test, and convince themselves they didn't.</p>
      <p>The labs are how I study this directly. The reports and notes are what comes out.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <SectionHead marker="FOCUS" title="Current focus" />

  <div class="page-grid">
    <div class="extended measure-tight">
      <p>Through 2026, verification depth in autonomous engineering systems. The premise: most multi-agent labs collapse because they grade themselves, and self-grading creates a flat verification surface that any sufficiently capable optimizer can climb without solving the underlying problem.</p>
      <p>The actual work is figuring out which structural fixes disrupt this and which are ceremonial. External verdicts, pre-registered falsifiers, adversarial payoffs. Cycles compare which holds.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <SectionHead marker="BACKGROUND" title="Background" />

  <div class="page-grid">
    <div class="extended measure-tight">
      <p>UW Madison alum. Currently running autonomous AI labs full-time and writing up what I find.</p>
      <p>The labs are not affiliated with UW Madison or any prior employer. No university resources, IP, or infrastructure are used in this work.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

</Default>
